(From update of attachment 263506)
>-    $query .= " " . $dbh->sql_group_by("test_". $obj ."s.". $obj ."_id", join(', ', @groupby));
>+    unshift(@groupby, "test_${obj}s.${obj}_id");
>+    $query .= " " . $dbh->sql_group_by(join(', ', @groupby));

For the record, I just realized that this fix is wrong. The problem is that join(", ", @groupby) is always defined, even if @groupby is empty, and this confuses sql_group_by() which incorrectly appends a comma at the end of the list. This generates an invalid SQL query on PostgreSQL. MySQL is not affected as it ignores the 2nd argument.

The correct fix is:

my $groupby;
$groupby = join(', ', @groupby) if scalar(groupby);
$query .= " " . $dbh->sql_group_by("test_". $obj ."s.". $obj ."_id", $groupby);

Please land this asap. Thanks! :)

