Bugzilla supports local usernames without a fully
qualified email address. This is done by setting the
"emailregexp:" parameter in the editparams.cgi to
"^[^@]+$" and the "emailsuffix:" to @mydomain.com.

Bugzilla comments the emailsuffix field with the
following, "This is a string to append to any email
addresses when actually sending mail to that address.
It is useful if you have changed the emailregexp param
to only allow local usernames, but you want the mail to
be delivered to username@my.local.hostname."

Partial remedial instructions follow:

Open
tr_testrunner/templates/en/default/tr_testrunner/test-runs-run-plan.html.tmpl

and comment out the following lines of code, like this:

// var manager = document.getElementById('manager').value;
// if (manager=='' ||
(!manager.match(/\w{1}[\w\-\.]*\@[\w\-\.]+/))) {
// alert('Please enter a valid manager');
// return false;
// }

then run the install script (tr_install.pl) again.

Now open the file tr_btpm_util.pl. Look for the sub
tr_detaint_email, and replace it by this code:

sub tr_detaint_email {
#$_[0] =~ /(\w{1}[\w\-\.]*)\@([\w\-\.]+)/;
$_[0] =~ /(\w{1}[\w\-\.]*)/;
$_[0] = "$1";
return (defined($_[0]));
}

