If a user tries to delete a test case from a run for example, the same message is used to describe a failure to delete the test case.  This is caused by the candelete function in TestCaseRun.pm called from tr_list_caseruns.cgi.  Here is the function:
sub candelete {
    my $self = shift;
    return 1 if Bugzilla->user->in_group('admin');
    return 0 unless Bugzilla->params->{"allow-test-deletion"};
    return 1 if Bugzilla->user->in_group('Testers') && Bugzilla->params->{"testopia-allow-group-member-deletes"};
    return 1 if $self->run->plan->get_user_rights(Bugzilla->user->id) & TR_DELETE;
    return 0;
}

Different return values could be used to describe different error conditions and provide a more descriptive message to the end-user.

