(From update of attachment 391384)
>+        //Get the first 10000 test plans from the server, this query could possibly be optimized by passing the 'product_id' in the planStoreParams.
>+        var planStoreParams = {current_tab: 'plan', limit: 10000};
>+        var tps = new TestPlanStore(planStoreParams, true);

I don't like this idea. What this is doing is building up to 10000 plan objects server side and then sending them all to the client when they usually only need two or three tops. This is a major load for the client to process, not to mention the amount of data that has to go over the wire for this. 

I would rather include the plan name in the Test Case object. You can add it to the hash in the TO_JSON method in TestCase.pm

>+        function headerGroupRenderer(value,u,record,rowIndex,colIndex,store){
>+            var testPlanRecord = tps.getById(value);
>+            var testPlanName =  testPlanRecord ? '\"' + testPlanRecord.get("name") + '\"  ' : '';
>+            return value + ';  ' + testPlanName;
>+        };

When I test this on my installation it seems to always return a blank plan name. Using the method mentioned above though should negate the need for this lookup.

